THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The development of state land for a qualified
2 project or for cottages to provide services related to behavioral
3 health issues in children by the Campus for Hope Foundation, or its
4 successor organization, is:
5 (a) Exempt from the provisions of chapter 341 of NRS and not
6 subject to the oversight or involvement of the State Public Works
7 Division of the Department of Administration; and
8 (b) Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, exempt from
9 the provisions of chapter 338 of NRS.
10 2. The provisions of NRS 338.013 to 338.090, inclusive, apply
11 to any contract awarded to a contractor or subcontractor by the
12 Campus for Hope Foundation, or its successor organization, for the
13 development of state land for a qualified project in the same manner
14 as if a public body had awarded the contract.
15 3. As used in this section:
16 (a) “Development” includes, without limitation, any
17 construction, improvement, repair, demolition, reconstruction,
18 acquisition, equipment, operation or maintenance related to the
19 qualified project or the cottages to provide services related to
20 behavioral health issues in children by the Campus for Hope
21 Foundation, or its successor organization.
22 (b) “Qualified project” has the meaning ascribed to it in
23 NRS 231.3723.
24 (c) “State land” means that portion of the real property
25 commonly known as the Southern Nevada Adult Mental Health
26 Services Campus which includes Clark County parcel numbers 163-
27 02-601-007 and 163-02-601-005.
28 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.
